==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simile
<hw>Sim"i*le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Similes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., from
<ets>similis</ets>. See <er>Similar</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A word or phrase by which anything is likened, in one or more of
its aspects, to something else; a similitude; a poetical or imaginative
comparison.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A good swift <qex>simile</qex>, but something currish.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Similiter</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
